 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uyales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yales</A> at: 8/20/02 11:07:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/utmayes1965.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tmayes1965</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/22/02 1:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Diminished nuclear weaponry.</span><hr size=1> Yales<br>
The biggest U.S nuclear explosion was 50 megatons.<br>
This test took place in 1963 in the south Pacific<br>
ocean.<br>
A 3 stage H-bomb has a fission primary, a bottle of fusion<br>
fuel, and an inner jacket/casing  made of U 238.<br>
A two stage h-bomb has just a fission primary, and <br>
a bottle of fusion fuel but no  U 238 jacket.<br>
A fusion boosted A-bomb has a little bit of lithium<br>
6 dueteride or tritium inside the core of a hollow pit to boost the fission yield by providing extra neutrons during the<br>
fission chain reaction.<br>
Tim.<br>
