The biggest soviet explosion was that of Czar bomba,which  was 58 megatons in 1961. Both of these explosions are recorded in the Guiness book of world records.The biggest U.S device was 50 megatons not 15 megatons.The  U 238<br>
inner jacket is usually a third stage. It is not always part<br>
of the secondary, but it can be , if you use a U 238<br>
bottle to contain the fusion fuel. Two stage clean  h-bombs<br>
do not use U 238 jackets and U 238  bottles.They use a fission<br>
primary, and then the fusion fuel is placed inside of a bottle <br>
made of a heavy metal such as lead. The only fission in a clean device occurrs only in the primary.Some examples<br>
of clean H-bombs are those tested by the british in 1958.<br>
The 15 megaton  bravo bomb of 1954 was dirty, because it had  a fission primary , it had fusion fuel stored in a U 238 bottle and it also had  an inner casing of U 238.<br>
The 25 megaton Mk-41 used the same basic design as bravo<br>
 with more fuel in it.<br>
<br>
In a dirty H-bomb 50% or more of the yield comes<br>
from nuclear fission, and not from fusion.<br>
Here is a hypothetical example:<br>
I have a 20 kiloton Pu 239 implosion type primary.<br>
Then I have 500 kilograms of lithium six dueteride<br>
stored inside a 100 kilogram U 238 bottle.<br>
Then I have a 100 kilogram inner jacket made of U 238.<br>
The primary explodes releases 20 kilotons.<br>
The 500 kilograms of fusion fuel fuses, and releases<br>
10 kilotons of yield per pound. This generates from  11<br>
to 22 megatons of yield. Then the high energy neutrons<br>
released by nuclear fusion in the secondary , cause<br>
nuclear fission to occurr in the U 238 bottle, and<br>
in the inner u 238 Jacket  .The U 238 fission<br>
jacket releases about 18 kilotons per pound of weight.<br>
The fission of the 1000 kilogram U 238 inner metal<br>
 Jacket thus  release 40 more more megatons of yield.<br>
The result is a a very dirty 3 stage   thermonuclear explosion with a yield of from 50 to 60 megatons that would be similiar to the soviet czar bomba of 1961. This explosion will <br>
 hurl  at least 50 to 60 million tons of intensely radioactive fallout into the atmosphere that will cover a vast area,<br>
just like czar bomba did for the soviets in 1961.<br>
All this fallout descending over Siberia, and the northern soviet union  may have lead the soviets to support,<br>
and sign  the limited nuclear weapon test ban treaty of 1963.<br>
This what a dirty H-bomb  does, and what it actually is<br>
like<br>
